{"id": "EUVD-2022-55321", "enisaUuid": "b10d06f3-0933-3405-a87c-f1c42f809ef8", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nASoC: SOF: Intel: hda: Fix potential buffer overflow by snprintf()\n\nsnprintf() returns the would-be-filled size when the string overflows\nthe given buffer size, hence using this value may result in the buffer\noverflow (although it's unrealistic).\n\nThis patch replaces with a safer version, scnprintf() for papering\nover such a potential issue.", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T12:30:45", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-13T21:31:18", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6ee1310f4d148dbf04c4159b88afd0b941018903", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f7915c5614a7ece117ec390f21a410531eac48de", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/94c1ceb043c1a002de9649bb630c8e8347645982", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50050"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50050"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "427241d2-e706-3ca8-a684-99a9b180ab97", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "29c8e4398f02adacd429c7847dacc8aea5a0c2f1 <94c1ceb043c1a002de9649bb630c8e8347645982"}, {"id": "4ba76cd3-5f86-3363-a79a-c67cdd382bca", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19.4"}, {"id": "5f6491a6-c7fe-36f2-b0cc-c4ecab901f72", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0"}, {"id": "65699720-5983-36af-960f-6d470e1e9197", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "29c8e4398f02adacd429c7847dacc8aea5a0c2f1 <f7915c5614a7ece117ec390f21a410531eac48de"}, {"id": "acb89a4f-0882-3f60-beab-15d51abd3058", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.10"}, {"id": "ae3a4e2b-0ea0-319c-8bdd-a4f1b41c494e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.63"}, {"id": "be10c1f8-0695-3222-a726-83e63466c9a1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "29c8e4398f02adacd429c7847dacc8aea5a0c2f1 <6ee1310f4d148dbf04c4159b88afd0b941018903"}, {"id": "fa6